			<title>Interviews with a few of Bordeaux's Wine Experts</title>
			<itunes:author>Frank Mangio - Taste Of Wine TV</itunes:author>
			<description>Over 700 million bottles of Bordeaux wine are produced every year, ranging from large quantities of everyday table wine, to some of the most expensive and prestigious wines in the world. 

Most Bordeaux wine is red, but sweet white wines have also contributed to the region's reputation, and dry white, rosé and sparkling wines (Crémant de Bordeaux) are also produced. Bordeaux wine is made in 9,000 wineries usually called châteaux from the grapes of 13,000 grape growers. 

There are 57 appellations of Bordeaux wine.&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/LearnAboutWineAndWineriesInSouthernCalif/~4/e4uGKdGaMKc" height="1" width="1"/&gt;</description>
